And George Thompson was the author of it. You know, George Thompson the grocer. And he had a lovely the Hermit of Warkworth. That's the hermitage cave you know. The history of that is in it. I think I gave it to me sist
er-in-law. I have had two or three but I have always given them away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5850145 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7222697\charrsid14627296 You almost know it off by heart!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1930389 JD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7222697\charrsid14627296 It's rather funny, all the years I have lived in Warkworth, I've never \{BLANK\} over \{BLANK\}
