wn so much about it. George Thompson was again the author and he used to lecture on it you know. And then we had these debating societies you know. We used to get the whole thing over there. The whole history. We had a broadcast here, the broadcast, I.T.V
.
 you know. And they interviewed several of the people. Oh it was good! The only thing that spoiled it they showed you, on the television, Warkworth Station, broken windows, derelict platforms and everything. And I thought that wasn't showing much beauty a
bout it.
